<br>
Effects of large buffs....<br>
<br>
Str &gt;&gt;&gt; Attack and higher max damage.  about 4-7% overall increase with maxed str.  Can carry more.  Skill checks for Smithing if greater than int/wis.<br>
<br>
Dex &gt;&gt;&gt; More Procs, faster learning of weapon skills.  Improves Archery, is the skill check for fletching if Wis/Int is lower, affects tailoring.<br>
<br>
Agility &gt;&gt;&gt; Improves AC, and damage avoidance rolls (dodge and the like).  Faster learning of defensive skills.<br>
<br>
Stamina &gt;&gt;&gt; Increases hitpoints.  If over 100 (101 plus) you have no negative affect of your stamina bar being empty except that you cant jump.<br>
<br>
Intelligence &gt;&gt;&gt; size of your mana pool for int casters.  Skill checks for most tradeskills if higher than wisdom.<br>
<br>
Wisdom &gt;&gt;&gt; size of your mana pool for wis casters.  Skill checks for most tradeskills if higher than int.<br>
<br>
Charisma &gt;&gt;&gt; Affects charm spells.  If over 105 (106 plus) you will get maximum vendor prices when selling, and minimum when buying if faction is at least indifferent.  <br>
<br>
If you do tradeskills it is generally worthwhile to keep a kit of int or wis gear to swap out.  For everyone iot is worthwhile getting a charisma set up for buying and selling.<br>
