Agility is about 60 points higher than it should be -- You get an AC bonus for it, up until it's around 120 points, or so.  After that, it's like 1 point of ac, for 30 points of agility -- Useless.  Stamina is the -real- stat that you need to focus on, as a high level Rogue.  I'd love to get mine to 255.  But seeing as to how I know longer play on Tunare... the odds of that happening are pretty slim.<br>
<br>
Not to mention, most players on -normal- servers have a Primal weapon, if they've been level 60 for 3 months.  It procs Avatar.  That's about 100 str, 100 dex, 100 agi, 150-200atk(depending on what other +atk items you're wearing)...<br>
<br>
So, you could have 155 str, 155 dex, 155 Agility.  Then go for say like.... 200ish stamina.  When the Primal proc'd (Trust me, they proc non-stop, and even more, after they've proc'd -- high dex)... You'd end up with 255 str, 255 dex, 255 agility and 200 stamina.  In my opinion, that should be the 'goal' for higher level 'raiding' rogues on this game.<br>
<br>
Keep in mind, I have 160 Stamina, as a Wood Elf.  If I had been a barbarian, I'd probably have 190-200ish.  Depending on what I equipped.  I don't suggest playing a Barbarian, though <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    the filthy brutes!<br>
<br>
Now, for Hybrids and Casters, I couldn't really tell you.  I wouldn't want to go all out stats, then have like 120 intelligence, if I was a Shadow Knight.  But then again, I've never played that class past level 30.  I have no idea what stats they really need to focus on.<br>
<br>
Also, take note, that -most- Rogues' stats tend to be 'higher' than that of warriors, and other 'tank' classes, due to the fact they -generally- use items that are piled with Str, Dex, Agi and next to no AC/HP.  In my opinion, hit points/stamina are -the- most important stat for a raiding Rogue.  <br>
<br>
Those AEs don't hurt as bad, when you have 5-6K Hit Points buffed.  Or those Ripostes for 600-1200 damage -- You can't always be -behind- the mob, especially on casters.  You have to fight on the same side as the tanks, in order to 'push' and interrupt their castings.  <br>
<br>
Now, if you're not a raiding Rogue.  You could probably get by on Mrylokars/Assassin's.  AC is actually better, for a normal experience group, than hit points.  At least in my opinion.  I don't mention SV, because -most- Rogues tend to have -all- SV in the 85ish range, unbuffed, with normal gear.  At least on a normal server <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
